{"id": "1414694517868724315", "channel_id": "1326453763355185215", "author_id": "581853263771467788", "author_name": "talecrafter8625", "content": "Sorry for the slow answer! I'm at work lol ^^;\n\nI think the only things that really stood out to me were the change in spelling of \"Koum\" to \"Koom\" between chapters 3 and 4, and the pervasive use of \"guys\" (\"you guys\", \"those guys\", \"a weird guy\", etc.). The latter felt a bit jarring at times when coming from certain characters, but that might just be a personal nitpick\n\nI also agree with CD in that the description of the Hellhound's motivation/appearance/operation were rather vague, but I interpreted it as an intentional narrative choice. The rule of only being able to meet it three times before it Gets You was consistent throughout the chapter, but everything else felt kinda fuzzy. Overall, it felt more like a \"ticking clock\" mechanism behind the central conflict than an active antagonist. But, if that's what the story was going for, I'd say it did that very well lol", "timestamp": "2025-09-08T19:30:56.813000+00:00", "type": 19, "mentions": ["88644018673582080"], "reply_to": "1414677075318673509"}
{"id": "1414694917367660725", "channel_id": "1326453763355185215", "author_id": "581853263771467788", "author_name": "talecrafter8625", "content": "TL;DR: There were a couple nitty-gritty things (I've also noticed that pronouns seem to get mixed up a lot), but I don't think the overall narrative was harmed considerably <:thumbsup:1356086340298473574>", "timestamp": "2025-09-08T19:32:32.061000+00:00"}
